      .default-text
        h2 Browsing 3 ways
        p There are at least 3 possible ways to build the browsing experience, and I wireframed all of them in low fidelity. Without testing, it's difficult to know which of these 3 approaches is preferable.

        h3 Approach 1: Map
        p Display a map view that shows the volume and concentration of pets. This lets users browse with a focus on dogs that are readily availale, and in configurations that make it easy to meet the maximum number of dogs in the smallest period of time.

        h3 Approach 2: Categories
        p Display dynamic categories of dogs based on the user's stated preferences. As they interact with listings, the categories can morph and improve to become a better match. Think spotify discover, but for dog profiles.

        h3 Approach 3: Focus
        p The previous two approaches follow pathways that eventually lead to viewing profiles directly. It's possible that the best approach is to skip directly to that step. Doing so forces users to focus on a single dog at a time, in a way that is photo-intensive and thus emotionally intense.
